Class BizResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.navis.framework.portal.BizResponse
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IAttributeHolder<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>, MessageCollector, java.io.Serializable

    public class BizResponse
extends java.lang.Object
implements MessageCollector, java.io.Serializable
    Encapsulates a response formed by the Business Tier in response to a request from the Presentation Tier.

      • getCreatedPrimaryKey

        @Nullable
public java.io.Serializable getCreatedPrimaryKey()
        Extracts and returns the primary key of a newly created entity from the response object.

        Only valid for BizRequests with a CrudTuple indexed with null! (This corresponds with a Request generated by CrudDelegate.requestCreate())

        Returns:
        the primary key of the entity just created

        Returns the QueryResult embedded in the BizResponse.

        Note: In case the BizResponse has no failures, the query result must never be null.

      • getValueObjects

        @Deprecated
public java.util.List getValueObjects(java.lang.String inEntityClass)
        Deprecated. use getQueryResult() or getQueryResult(inKey) instead.
        Public accessor method retrieves a list of ValueObjects for a given entity class (inEntityClass).

        If the caller wants to obtain the entire list of ValueObjects in the response, he should call the same method with no arguments (getValueObjects())

      • getValueObjects

public java.util.List getValueObjects()

        Public accessor method retrieves the entire list of ValueObjects contained in the response.

        Call this instead of getValueObjects(entityClass) when you want the entire list.

      • getMessages

        public java.util.List getMessages(MessageLevel inSeverity)
        Description copied from interface: MessageCollector
        Returns all messages of type UserMessage at specified level. Always returns a collection, an empty one if none exist. The collection is a detached and hence changing the collection does not change the MessageCollector. However changing the entries will. For a severe list, will not include overridden errors.
        Specified by:
        getMessages in interface MessageCollector
